31: caMonBusReceiveSysDfax                   [] //  ACCont bus voltage report Dfax Reference Subsystem Name (caBusMaxDfaxMode=1)

 6: SensCutOffLoad                        0.030 // Detailed report Load Distribut.factors cutoff [0-1]

 9: monCutOff                                50 // Max number times to report the same branch conting Violations
10: MaxNumGenInPool                          30 // Max N of gens for Dhelp/Dharm reports
11: MaxGenInPool                           5000 // MW cutoff to skip reporting generators for Dhelp/Dharm reports for big generator pools
12: SensCutOffMode                            0 // 0-traditional single cutoff for base and cont.  1-separate cutoffs for base and cont

14: SensCutOffCont                        0.030 // Dfax cutoff for post-contingency [0.00 to 1.00]. Only used if SensCutOffMode1.  Otherwise uses SensCutoff for both base and cont.

12: SensCutOffMode                            0 // 0-traditional single cutoff for base and cont.  1-separate cutoffs for base and cont
13: SensCutOffBase                        0.030 // Dfax cutoff for pre-contingency [0.00 to 1.00]. Only used if SensCutOffMode=1.  Otherwise uses SensCutoff for both base and cont.
14: SensCutOffCont                        0.030 // Dfax cutoff for post-contingency [0.00 to 1.00]. Only used if SensCutOffMode1.  Otherwise uses SensCutoff for both base and cont.

 9: monCutOff                                50 // Max number times to report the same branch conting Violations

11: MaxGenInPool                           5000 // MW cutoff to skip reporting generators for Dhelp/Dharm reports for big generator pools
12: SensCutOffMode                            0 // 0-traditional single cutoff for base and cont.  1-separate cutoffs for base and cont
13: SensCutOffBase                        0.030 // Dfax cutoff for pre-contingency [0.00 to 1.00]. Only used if SensCutOffMode=1.  Otherwise uses SensCutoff for both base and cont.
14: SensCutOffCont                        0.030 // Dfax cutoff for post-contingency [0.00 to 1.00]. Only used if SensCutOffMode1.  Otherwise uses SensCutoff for both base and cont.
